manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: ASUS is one of Fortune magazine’s World’s Most Admired Companies and is one of the top motherboard and gaming brands, as well as a top-three consumer notebook vendor. ASUS is driven by passion and innovation and dedicated to creating quality products for a future smart life, designing and manufacturing products that perfectly meet the needs of today's digital home, office and person. Our wide portfolio includes MG248Q, Chromebox and a range of devices and components, along with AR and VR. PRIME Z790-P WIFI D4 ASUS PRIME Z790-P WIFI D4 LGA 1700 ATX motherboard with PCIe 5.0, three M.2 slots, 14+1 DrMOS, DDR4, Intel WIFI 6, Realtek 2.5 Gb LAN, HDMI, DP, USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C, front USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type-C, Thunderbolt (USB4) support, Arua Sync Intel LGA 1700 socket: Ready for 12th and 13th Gen Intel processors Enhanced power solution: 14+1 DrMOS, 6-layer PCB, ProCool connectors, alloy chokes and durable capacitors for stable power delivery Next-gen connectivity: Intel Wi-Fi 6, PCIe 5.0, Realtek 2.5Gb Ethernet, USB 3.2 Gen2x2 Type-C, front panel USB 3.2 Gen 2 Type-C, Thunderbolt (USB4) header support, 3 PCIe 4.0 M.2 ASUS OptiMem II: Careful routing of traces and vias, plus ground layer optimizations to preserve signal integrity for improved memory overclocking Comprehensive cooling: Large VRM heatsinks, flexible M.2 heatsink, PCH heatsink, hybrid fan headers and Fan Xpert 4 with AI Cooling II

AI Cooling ll AI Cooling II balances the thermals and acoustics of any build with a single click. A proprietary ASUS algorithm slashes unnecessary noise while running a quick stress test, and then it monitors CPU temperatures to dynamically adjust fans to optimal speeds. M.2 Heatsinks An M.2 heatsink takes care of the two M.2 slots, warding off throttling that can occur with M.2 storage during sustained transfers. Removable captive screws reduce risk of drops or loss during heatsink removal. VRM Heatsinks and Thermal Pads The extensive surface area of the massive heatsinks cover the VRMs and chokes to improve heat dissipation. Together with specially engineered thermal pads, they improve heat transfer from the MOSFETs and chokes for better cooling performance.

Robust Power Design Stable power is essential to extract every last bit of performance out of Intel processors. The PRIME Z790-P WIFI D4 is geared to cater to the demands of these high-core-count CPUs. 1. ProCool Connectors Proprietary connectors augment the motherboard's link to the PSU with 4 pin + 8 pin connectors that pass 12 volts of power directly to the processors. Each jack features solid pins that can handle more current than hollow-pin connectors. 2. 14 + 1 Teamed Power Stages A VRM with 14 + 1 DrMOS delivers the power and efficiency that the latest Intel processors demand. DDR4 DDR4 5333 (OC) Improvements to trace routing design provide the latest Intel processors with enhanced access to memory bandwidth. ASUS OptiMem II technology carefully maps memory signal pathways across different PCB layers to reduce path distance, and it adds shielding zones that significantly reduce crosstalk. Three M.2 slots (up to 64 Gbps) PRIME Z790-P WIFI D4 offers a total of three M.2 slots that support data-transfer speeds of up to 64 Gbps via PCIe 4.0, enabling quicker boot-up and app load times with OS or application drives.

PCIe 5.0 Slot PCIe 5.0 offers twice the data transfer speed of PCIe 4.0, making it robust enough to handle new data-heavy tasks. PCIe 5.0 also brings other benefits, such as electrical changes to improve signal integrity, backward-compatible CEM connectors for add-in cards, and compatibility with previous versions of PCI Express. USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C A batch of USB ports support high-end rigs loaded with peripherals, including the rear USB Type-C connectors with ultrafast USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 for transmission speeds of up to 20 Gbps. WiFi 6E The Intel WiFi 6 module is compatible with the 802.11ax standard and pushes theoretical peak bandwidth up to an incredible 2.4 Gbps. Perhaps more importantly for power users, it's optimized for more efficient operation on crowded networks with a lot of competing traffic. Pair your motherboard with ASUS WiFi 6 routers to fully experience the networking potential of WiFi 6.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars ASUS Prime Z790-P WiFi D4: Robust Performance and Future-Ready Design!
reviews.reviewText: ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️The ASUS Prime Z790-P WiFi D4 LGA 1700 motherboard is a stellar choice for anyone looking to build a high-performance system with Intel's 14th, 12th, or 13th Gen processors. This ATX motherboard combines robust features, reliable performance, and a future-ready design that sets it apart from the competition.The inclusion of WiFi D4 ensures seamless wireless connectivity, eliminating the need for additional adapters and providing convenience in networking. The LGA 1700 socket is designed to support a range of Intel processors, making it a versatile option for different performance requirements.One standout feature is the robust power delivery system, providing stable power to the CPU for optimal performance and overclocking capabilities. The ASUS Prime Z790-P is built with high-quality components, enhancing its durability and reliability for long-term use.The ATX form factor offers plenty of expansion options, allowing users to customize their system with additional components and peripherals. The motherboard's layout is well-designed, with accessible ports and connectors for easy installation and cable management.The BIOS interface is user-friendly and provides advanced customization options for enthusiasts and overclockers. The motherboard's compatibility with high-speed DDR4 memory ensures efficient multitasking and fast data access.Additionally, ASUS has a reputation for excellent customer support and a reliable warranty, adding peace of mind to your purchase.In conclusion, the ASUS Prime Z790-P WiFi D4 LGA 1700 motherboard stands out as a top choice for those seeking a high-performance motherboard with future-proofing capabilities. Whether you're a gamer, content creator, or power user, this motherboard delivers on both functionality and reliability, making it a worthwhile investment for your next PC build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It works good.
reviews.reviewText: What I found out that may be helpful is if you use XMP function in the bios you can only use 2 dimm slots and with this ddr4 version of mobo you are maxed at ddr4 3200. It won't boot with xmp on and 4 dimm slots in use. I had 4 ddr4 3200 ram and they were running at 2100 when i looked in bios and everything booted and worked great. Well I went to turn xmp on to achieve the 3200 speed they were rated at and the mobo was rated for and the computer wouldn't post. After research I found you can only use 2 of the dimm slots if you are using xmp. After going to 2 dimm and xmp on everything was great again. My previous asus mobo (older 2017 chipset) I took these ram from did great with these 4 dimms and xmp on so it's a quirk of this mobo. It still is a great value and you can easily just put 2 32gig ddr4 3200 and be fine.I was trying to reuse old ram so I bought this ddr4 version and I may have just upgraded to the ddr5 mobo instead if I knew my ram wouldn't work as i had intended. I'll never use that much ram anyways so it worked out luckily for me otherwise I'd be upset if id bought 4 dimms for this board and couldn't use xmp. Hopefully this saves some poor soul time and money.
